  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "Security update for the Linux Kernel",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "\n\nThe SUSE Linux Enterprise 11 SP4 kernel was updated to receive various security and bugfixes.\n\nThis update is only provided as a fix update for IBM Z platform.\n\n- CVE-2017-5753 / 'Spectre Attack': IBM Z fixes were included but not enabled in the previous update. This update enables those fixes.\n- CVE-2017-5715 / 'Spectre Attack': IBM Z fixes were already included in the previous update. A bugfix for the patches has been applied on top.\n- CVE-2017-5754: The IBM Z architecture is not affected by the 'Meltdown' attack.\n\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
